---------------------------------Detective A’s Puzzles

Detective A’s Study
Desk Riddle
Riddle: “I am the key to the past, yet I hold the future. What am I?”
Solution: The diary hides a secret compartment containing a key.
Knowledge Needed: Spot the diary among the papers and inspect it for hidden catches.
Torn Portrait Riddle
Riddle: “I see without eyes, and I speak without a mouth. What am I?”
Solution: The portrait bears invisible ink—illumination by the oil lamp reveals the hidden message.
Knowledge Needed: Realize you must light/position the lamp to make invisible ink appear.


Hidden Library
Chest Riddle
Riddle: “I am not alive, but I grow; I don’t have lungs, but I need air; I don’t have a mouth, but water kills me. What am I?”
Solution: Fire—lighting the candle next to the chest triggers its opening mechanism.
Knowledge Needed: Understand classic fire-riddle and use the flickering candle.
Ancient Tomes Riddle
Riddle: “I speak without a tongue, and I hear without ears. I have no body, but I come alive with the wind. What am I?”
Solution: An echo—whisper into the correct book (the one with the echo symbol) to activate a secret passage.
Knowledge Needed: Identify which tome bears the echo-symbol and speak toward it.


-----------------------------------Detective B’s Puzzles

Detective B’s Laboratory
Chalkboard Riddle
Riddle: “I am always hungry, I must always be fed. The finger I touch will soon turn red. What am I?”
Solution: Fire—naming it (or lighting a flame) unlocks a hidden compartment in the chalkboard frame.
Knowledge Needed: Spot the concealed latch and know the classic fire riddle.
Blood-stained Table Riddle
Riddle: “I have keys but no locks. I have space but no room. You can enter, but you can’t go outside. What am I?”
Solution: A keyboard—leading you to the computer terminal where “Eternalis” data resides.
Knowledge Needed: Recognize the riddle’s answer and search the terminal for deeper clues.



Security Room
Safe Riddle
Riddle: “The more of me you take, the more you leave behind. What am I?”
Solution: Footsteps—entering that word (or mimicking it) unlocks the safe to reveal crucial evidence.
Knowledge Needed: Recall the riddle and apply it to the combination lock.
CCTV Screens Riddle
Riddle: “I am not alive, but I can grow. I don’t have lungs, but I need air. I don’t have a mouth, but water kills me. What am I?”
Solution: Fire—entering “fire” into the CCTV interface brings up additional camera feeds, showing hidden passages.
Knowledge Needed: Map the repeating “fire” riddle to the security system’s code input.

------------------------------------------Cooperative Puzzles

Bookshelf Mechanism (Library)
Challenge: Four books bear planetary symbols; they must be pulled in numerical order.
Co-op Solution:
A notes the symbols on the book spines.
B reads the symbol→number table on the lab chalkboard.
A pulls books in the order B provides (e.g. Sun=1, Mercury=2…).
Result: The shelf swings open, revealing the hidden corridor.
Crest & Button Puzzle (Grand Ballroom)
Challenge: Two halves of Blackwood’s crest and two synchronized buttons lock the exit.
Co-op Solution:
A and B each place their half-crest into the corresponding recess on their side of the door.
They press their buttons simultaneously on opposite sides.
Result: The bolts retract and the final chamber opens.


Co-op Puzzles (require both detectives)
Bookshelf Sequence (Library mechanism)
Crest & Synchronized Buttons (Grand Ballroom exit)